Comment: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{=14}===============================DIALOGUE============================
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.01,0:01:55.57,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Fogo!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.57,0:01:57.72,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Hey, everyone! Wake up! - OG}Ei, todo mundo! Levantem!{Gal}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.72,0:02:01.44,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Droga...! Isso foi coisa dos piratas?{OG}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.44,0:02:04.65,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{There must still be a lot of people left inside! - OG}Ainda tem muita gente lá dentro!{Gal}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.65,0:02:07.94,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Where's Iceburg-san?!\NWhat's going on upstairs?! - OG}Cadê o Iceburg?!\NO que está acontecendo lá em cima?!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.94,0:02:09.11,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Vamos verificar!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.82,0:02:14.19,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Hurry! The rest of you, put out the fire! - OG}Rápido! O resto, apaguem o fogo!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.48,0:02:23.85,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Looks like the fire has started to spread. - OG}Parece que o fogo começou a se espalhar.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.42,0:02:31.38,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{I don't know if you're\Na leopard human or what, but... - OG}Não me importa se é um homem leopardo ou o quê...{Z/Gal}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.15,0:02:35.01,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{I won't let you lay a hand on Iceburg-[/i1]san[/i0]! - OG}Não vou deixar você encostar no Iceburg!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.88,0:02:40.97,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Oh, no...! Carnivore Zoan\Ntypes become more brutal!}Ah não...! Zoans carnívoros\Nsão mais brutais que os outros!{Gal/Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.46,0:02:47.27,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Isso mesmo. Tipos Logia,\Nzoan e paramecia...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.27,0:02:49.86,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Many unique powers exist. - OG}Seus poderes são variados e únicos.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.43,0:02:56.73,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Genuine physical augmentation\Nis the trait of Zoan types. - OG}Mas o tipo zoan é o único que oferece\Naumento físico puro.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.73,0:03:00.41,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Quanto mais treinamos, mais poder ganhamos.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.41,0:03:05.58,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{The Zoan type is the strongest species\Nwhen it comes to a close attack. - OG}Zoans são muito superiores\Nem combate corpo a corpo.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.58,0:03:06.87,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Iceburg-[/i1]san[/i0]! - OG}Iceburg!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.87,0:03:08.50,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Capatazes!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.80,0:03:12.84,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Lucci... os carpinteiros estão subindo.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.33,0:03:16.47,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Don't worry. They can't make it this far. - OG}Não se preocupe. Não vão chegar até aqui.{Z/Gal}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.47,0:03:18.47,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{\fad(150,150)}Tempest Kick!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.65,0:03:31.49,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Go back! The ceiling is...! - OG}Voltem! O teto está prestes a...!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.33,0:03:42.16,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Nami!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.08,0:03:52.67,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Chopper!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.90,0:03:55.28,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Paulie, o que está fazendo?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.28,0:03:57.63,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{I'm taking you out of\Nthis place no matter what! - OG}De jeito nenhum que vou te deixar aqui!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.63,0:04:00.30,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{It's not possible! Your injuries\Nare too severe! How can you... - OG}Não pode! Não com esses ferimentos...!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.99,0:04:04.02,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Stop it, Paulie. - OG}Para, Paulie.{Gal}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.94,0:04:11.52,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Don't call my name... as if we're friends! - OG}Não diga meu nome... como se ainda fôssemos amigos!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.57,0:04:17.95,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Malditos...!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.44,0:04:20.65,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Por que tinha que ser vocês?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.59,0:04:22.41,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Eu...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.29,0:04:25.66,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{at least... - OG}Pelo menos, eu...{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.68,0:04:31.13,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{I considered you guys my friends all this time! - OG}Sempre considerei vocês meus amigos!{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.27,0:04:37.84,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{It was just you. -OG}O sentimento não era mútuo.{Z/Gal}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.73,0:04:52.15,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Desgraçado do pombo...!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.15,0:04:53.48,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Chapéu de Palha!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.14,0:05:01.73,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{\fad(150,150)}Finger Pistol.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.07,0:05:04.12,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Luffy!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.14,0:05:30.73,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Tenha um bom voo pra fora da ilha!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.07,0:05:37.98,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Luffy!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.80,0:05:42.36,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Seu desgraçado...!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.82,0:05:44.18,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{\fad(150,150)}Iron Body.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.20,0:06:01.38,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Zoro!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.90,0:06:11.27,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Você também.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.92,0:06:31.67,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Did you get everyone out of the building?! - OG}Tiraram todo mundo do prédio?!{Gal}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.67,0:06:35.50,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{We can't go inside anymore!\NHave each team account for its men! - OG}Não dá mais pra entrar!\NCada equipe faça a contagem dos seus!{Gal}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.50,0:06:39.62,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Hey, where's Iceburg-[/i1]san[/i0]?\NDid you see him? - OG}Ei, cadê o Iceburg? Vocês o viram?{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.62,0:06:42.27,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Don't tell me he's still in this fire... - OG}Não me diz que ele ainda está lá dentro com esse fogo...!{Z/JT}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.27,0:06:43.42,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Tenho certeza que ele está bem!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.30,0:06:47.39,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Three of our foremen are with him.\NThere's no way he got left in there. - OG}Três capatazes estavam com ele;\Nimpossível terem deixado ele pra trás.{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.39,0:06:49.32,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Vocês vão checar ali também!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.00,0:06:55.14,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Essa mulher...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.96,0:06:59.11,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,É uma dos Chapéus de Palha. Tenho certeza!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.64,0:07:02.00,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Ela pulou de uma janela?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.00,0:07:05.40,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{She was probably surrounded by flames\Nand had trouble escaping. - OG}Deve ter escapado por pouco\Nquando as chamas a cercaram.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.27,0:07:08.29,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,O que fazemos com ela?{OG}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.29,0:07:12.58,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Seriously... what a terrible thing they've done.}Sério... Eles que causaram essa confusão.{Gal}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.58,0:07:14.90,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Vamos fazê-la dizer onde estão os outros!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.90,0:07:18.44,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{We'll capture all of them\Nand hand them over to the Marines! - OG}Vamos prender todos eles\Ne entregar pra Marinha!{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.91,0:07:24.11,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{What pirates say cannot be evidence. - OG}A palavra de um pirata não serve como evidência.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.11,0:07:26.82,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Esse incidente agora será encoberto pelas trevas.{OG}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.39,0:07:29.92,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Iceburg-[/i1]san[/i0]... - OG}Iceburg...{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.92,0:07:35.40,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{No matter how good of a shipbuilding engineer you are, or even if you're the mayor of a big city... - OG}Você pode ser um carpinteiro renomado\Ne prefeito de uma grande cidade...{Gal}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.14,0:07:41.06,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{you, a mere citizen, shouldn't have disobeyed\Nthe powerful World Government. - OG}mas você, um mero cidadão, não deveria ter\Ndesafiado o poderoso Governo Mundial.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.94,0:07:53.98,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Vamos. Vamos encontrar o outro\Naprendiz de Tom, Franky—{Gal/Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.98,0:07:58.79,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,ou melhor, Cutty Flam,\Ne pegar as plantas dele.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.18,0:08:16.93,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Vovó! Vovó! Tem um incêndio enorme!
Comment: 0,0:08:16.18,0:08:16.95,Secondary-207+,,0,0,0,,{Nyaa!}Meow!{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.95,0:08:21.15,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,É o escritório principal da Galley-La.\NQue coisa terrível de se fazer...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.09,0:08:26.48,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Coisa terrível? Alguém ateou fogo?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.48,0:08:29.11,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Well, I don't know... - OG}Bom, não tenho certeza...{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.11,0:08:33.20,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,mas muitas vezes, um mau pressentimento acaba se confirmando.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.20,0:08:35.58,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{I hope Iceburg is okay. - OG}Espero que o Iceburg esteja bem.{Gal}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.54,0:08:43.62,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Seriously, this is all because of that thing.\NIt just shouldn't exist. - OG}Sério, tudo isso por causa daquela coisa\Nque nem deveria existir.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.09,0:09:00.77,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Blueno... So Franky was at your bar? - OG}Blueno, você disse que o Franky estava no seu bar?{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.77,0:09:01.81,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,É.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.19,0:09:04.56,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Mas ele saiu correndo atrás do Chapéu de Palha.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.56,0:09:06.07,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Entendo.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.00,0:09:10.65,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Seems like he doesn't\Nstay in one place for long. - OG}Parece que ele não fica parado num lugar só.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.53,0:09:15.58,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{But people with bad timing really exist. - OG}Mas tem gente que realmente aparece\Nna hora e no lugar errado.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.88,0:09:17.58,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Look. - OG}Olhem ali.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.33,0:09:20.54,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Escutem, Chapéu de Palha!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.05,0:09:23.02,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{We've got Long-nose with us! - OG}Pegamos o narigudo!{Gal}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.02,0:09:25.00,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,É isso mesmo!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.00,0:09:27.65,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Se não quiser que a gente\Ncosture ele numa árvore–
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.65,0:09:30.35,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Idiot! That's not it! How many\Ntimes do I have to tell you?! - OG}Idiota! Como que você ainda não entendeu?{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.35,0:09:33.02,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{That's "If you don't want him\Nto sink in the sea"! - OG}É: "Se não quer que a gente\N{\i1}jogue{\i0} ele {\i1}no mar{\i0}!"{JT}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.02,0:09:33.92,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Costure ele {\i1}no{\i0}–
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.92,0:09:34.47,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{In the sea"! - OG}{\i1}Jogue{\i0} ele!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.93,0:09:37.89,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Geez, what were you listening to?! - OG}Droga, vocês sequer escutam?!{Gal}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.89,0:09:41.28,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{What's important is to get\Nthe message to Straw Hat, right?! - OG}O que importa é passar\Na mensagem pro Chapéu de Palha, certo?{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.28,0:09:43.39,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{We're saying that message ain't gonna work! - OG}Mas essa mensagem não vai funcionar!{Z/JT}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.39,0:09:45.11,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Bro is gonna beat you up. - OG}O Bro vai bater em vocês.{Gal}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.11,0:09:47.59,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{You say it like, "If you don't \Nwant him to sink in the sea, - OG}"Se não quer que a gente jogue ele no mar,{JT}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.59,0:09:50.51,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{come to the warehouse under the bridge! Franky sends his regards!" - OG}venha ao armazém debaixo da ponte! Assinado, Franky!"{Gal}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.51,0:09:51.53,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Entenderam?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.01,0:09:57.00,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Mind you, even if he comes,\NBro is gonna beat the crap out of him, though. - OG}Mesmo que ele venha, o Bro ainda\Nvai acabar com ele de qualquer jeito.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.80,0:10:03.84,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Who did you say is waiting for whom where? - OG}Quem disse que está esperando\Nquem e onde?{JT}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.84,0:10:06.60,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Hmm? Quem diabos é você?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.60,0:10:09.54,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{We're busy right now! Get lost! - OG}Estamos no meio de algo aqui, então rua!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.54,0:10:12.97,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{If you don't wanna die, answer my question in three seconds. - OG}Se não quiser morrer,\Ntem três segundos pra responder.{Z/Gal}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.97,0:10:15.66,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Hã?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.66,0:10:18.05,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{This guy's talking nonsense. - OG}Esse cara está delirando.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.05,0:10:20.64,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Do you know what family we're in? - OG}Não sabe quem somos?{Gal}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.13,0:10:27.21,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Which place do you mean\Nby the warehouse under the bridge? - OG}Onde fica esse armazém debaixo da ponte?{Gal}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.21,0:10:30.03,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,O Franky está lá, não é?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.00,0:10:34.67,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Que assunto você tem com o Bro?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.67,0:10:38.53,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{If you wanna talk to him,\Nthen talk to us first! - OG}Se quer falar com ele,\Nvai ter que falar com a gente primeiro.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.89,0:10:57.97,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{To think that you left the friends you traveled together with all the way from the East Blue, for the ship... - OG}{\q2}Não acredito que vocês vieram juntos do East Blue\Naté aqui só pra se separar por causa de um navio!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.28,0:11:01.89,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{What are you guys crying for? - OG}Por que {\i1}vocês{\i0} estão chorando?{Gal}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.89,0:11:05.01,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{You dummy! We're not crying, you dummy! - OG}Não seja idiota!\NNão estamos chorando, besta!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.01,0:11:10.20,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{But it's true that I was moved by your protecting this ship all by yourself while all those things were happening! - OG}É que foi muito emocionante ver você ficar firme\Ncom seu navio mesmo com tudo que aconteceu!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.20,0:11:11.94,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,– Não estamos chorando!\N– Não estamos chorando!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.94,0:11:13.92,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{None of us are crying! - OG}– Ninguém aqui está chorando!\N– Ninguém aqui está chorando!{Gal}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.92,0:11:16.44,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Qual é o problema deles?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.83,0:11:23.37,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Anyway, now you know that those guys\Nand I are no longer friends, right?! - OG}Enfim, vocês sabem que eu não sou mais\Namigo daqueles caras, certo?{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.75,0:11:26.08,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{I'll...}Aqui vai...{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.49,0:11:28.84,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{I'll sing about your hardships! - OG}Uma canção sobre suas dificuldades!{Gal}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.84,0:11:32.12,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{The song title is "Falling Out:\NNorthern Wind Chop!"}Se chama: "Separação: Golpe do Vento Norte!"{Gal}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.12,0:11:34.12,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,– Viva! Bro!\N– Viva! Bro!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.12,0:11:36.09,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Está tirando sarro de mim?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.32,0:11:47.00,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Ei, o chá já está pronto? Estou com sede.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.00,0:11:50.02,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{– Okay! We'll bring it right over!\N– Okay! We'll bring it right over! - OG}– Prontinho! Já vai!\N– Prontinho! Já vai!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.61,0:11:55.20,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{I'm exhausted from crying...\NNot that I cried, though. - OG}Estou exausto de chorar...\NNão que eu tenha chorado, né.{Gal}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.80,0:12:03.25,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Aqui, Bro. Tá um pouco quente.{OG}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.30,0:12:06.71,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Valeu.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.35,0:12:10.45,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Then, I get it, brother, you know... - OG}Tudo bem, entendo, irmãozinho. Sabe...{Gal}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.63,0:12:13.80,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Ai, tá quente!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.80,0:12:15.55,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Se acalma um pouco, vai!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.71,0:12:19.83,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{I'm sorry, Bro. - OG}Desculpa, Bro.{Gal}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.83,0:12:22.39,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Que tal descansar um pouco\Ne tomar um chá também?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.15,0:12:28.96,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Eu te entendo.{OG}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.96,0:12:34.48,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{You must be holding quite a grudge against us for taking 200 million belly away from you guys... - OG}Você deve guardar bastante rancor da gente por roubar seus 200 milhões de belly...{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.28,0:12:38.26,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{since it led to such a big fight. - OG}principalmente porque levou àquela briga toda.{Gal}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.08,0:12:42.19,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{It was meant to happen, that's all. - OG}O que aconteceu, aconteceu.{Gal}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.19,0:12:44.49,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Holding a grudge doesn't do me any good. -OG}Guardar rancor não me faz bem.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.51,0:12:47.41,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{You're a good sport. - OG}Você é gente boa.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.41,0:12:48.82,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Cool. - OG}Respeito.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.49,0:12:51.08,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{That 200 million... - OG}Mas aqueles 200 milhões...{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.99,0:12:54.66,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{I used it all, though! - OG}A gente gastou tudo!{Gal}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.66,0:12:56.30,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{You want me to knock you over? - OG}Quer que eu te derrube?{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.30,0:12:59.52,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Now, now... Don't get so upset. - OG}Calma, calma... Não fica assim.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.52,0:13:03.26,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Você me mostrou como é homem.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.26,0:13:08.36,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{So, now I have to calm my anger\Nover the complete destruction - OG}Então quer dizer que não posso ficar bravo\Npor minha casa e estaleiro de desmonte—{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.36,0:13:12.19,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{of the Franky House, which was my home\Nand demolition factory. - OG}minha querida Franky House—\Nterem sido {\i1}completamente{\i0} destruídos!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.08,0:13:16.70,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{On top of that, you guys\Nannihilated my subordinates! - OG}E ainda por cima, vocês bateram\Nnos meus subordinados até não poder mais!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.70,0:13:19.16,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{How dare you bastards?! - OG}Seus malditos desgraçados...!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.16,0:13:20.05,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Bro!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.05,0:13:22.24,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{The anger welled up! - OG}A raiva saiu!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.24,0:13:24.26,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Seus desgraçados!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.76,0:13:37.06,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Well, brother, although a lot happened, - OG}Sabe, irmãozinho, muita coisa aconteceu,{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.06,0:13:39.99,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{let's calm our anger towards\Neach other on this matter, - OG}mas devíamos parar de ficar\Nbravo um com o outro{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.99,0:13:43.70,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{and settle it as "Heave-ho! Heave-ho!" - OG}e deixar dragões comerem dragões.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.70,0:13:45.44,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{You mean "fifty-fifty." - OG}Você quer dizer "águas passadas".{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.44,0:13:47.39,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{You mean "fifty-fifty," Bro. - OG}É "águas passadas", Bro.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.77,0:13:53.20,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{What're you gonna do now that you're alone? - OG}E agora que está sozinho, o que vai fazer?{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.20,0:13:55.11,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{You have nowhere to go anyway, right? - OG}Não tem pra onde ir, certo?{Gal}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.11,0:13:59.61,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{If that's the case, I can take you in.\NCome work for me! - OG}Se for o caso, posso te acolher.\NVem trabalhar pra mim!{Gal}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.02,0:14:01.89,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Eu gosto de você.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.89,0:14:05.57,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{No way! I don't wanna become\Na demolition worker. - OG}Nem pensar! Não quero desmontar navios.{Gal}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.52,0:14:09.33,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Even though I left my group, I'm still a pirate! - OG}Mesmo tendo saído da tripulação, ainda sou pirata!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.00,0:14:14.42,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Here's one titled "Pirate's Creed." - OG}Aqui vai uma chamada "Credo do Pirata".{Gal}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.42,0:14:16.49,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,– Viva, Bro!\N– Viva, Bro!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.49,0:14:19.51,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Like I said, are you making fun of me?! - OG}Está tirando sarro de mim de novo!{Gal}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.00,0:14:24.60,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Geez... I'm trying to think what\Nyou should do next, for your sake! - OG}Poxa... Estou tentando te ajudar\Na descobrir o que fazer!{Gal}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.60,0:14:26.43,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Não é da sua conta!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.09,0:14:30.60,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Besides, is it okay for you\Nto relax in a place like this? - OG}Além disso, esse é o melhor lugar\Npra ficar relaxando agora?{Gal}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.60,0:14:32.43,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,A maré de tempestade está chegando, né?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.43,0:14:35.06,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,É, por isso mesmo...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.58,0:14:39.40,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,quando a Aqua Laguna chega,\Ntodos precisamos nos ajudar.{OG}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.41,0:14:46.69,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{From now until late into the night, houses will be submerged up to the second floor. - OG}Conforme a noite avança, o mar vai chegar\Naté o segundo andar das casas.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.69,0:14:51.27,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{If you're in the backstreets or capes\Nat a time like this, you don't stand a chance. - OG}Agora, quem estiver nas ruas dos fundos\Nou no cabo não tem chance.{Z/Gal}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.27,0:14:54.37,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{You don't have to worry\Nif you keep your ship here too. - OG}Não precisa se preocupar\Nse deixar seu navio aqui.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.72,0:14:58.08,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Ah... Obrigado... Agradeço.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.08,0:14:59.96,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{You dummy! Don't act like we're strangers! - OG}Seu idiota! Não aja como se fôssemos estranhos!{Z/JT}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.40,0:15:04.64,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{In any case, it must be tough\Nto have flood damage like that every year. - OG}De qualquer forma, deve ser difícil\Nlidar com enchente todo ano.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.64,0:15:08.80,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Well, everyone's used to\Nthis annual evacuation, though. - OG}Bom, a essa altura, todo mundo\Njá se acostumou com a evacuação anual.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.51,0:15:14.77,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{What's more problematic is that the water level of the sea \Nhas been increasing every year. - OG}O maior problema é que o nível\Ndo mar sobe a cada ano.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.77,0:15:17.77,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{The backstreet area you can see above the sea now -OG}A área das ruas dos fundos que\Nvocê vê acima do mar{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.77,0:15:23.28,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{is a town built on the rooftops of an old town that existed several hundred years ago. - OG}é uma cidade construída nos telhados de uma\Ncidade antiga de centenas de anos atrás.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.28,0:15:28.98,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{It's said that Shipyard Island and the backstreets were completely on one land a long time ago. - OG}{\q2}Dizem que a Ilha do Estaleiro e as ruas dos fundos\Neram uma única massa terrestre antigamente.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.98,0:15:33.25,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{But now, so much of the area is under water\Nthat it's called a floating city. - OG}Mas agora, tanto da ilha está submerso\Nque a chamam de cidade flutuante.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.79,0:15:36.83,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{All the sidewalks became canals. - OG}As calçadas viraram canais.{Gal}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.83,0:15:40.33,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Properly speaking, rather than saying that the water level is increasing, -OG}Tecnicamente, não é o nível\Nda água que está subindo,{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.33,0:15:43.30,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{they say that the foundation\Nof the island is sinking. - OG}mas sim a fundação da ilha que está afundando.{Gal}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.30,0:15:47.99,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{As it stands, the areas in town we can\Nlive in will get smaller and smaller. - OG}Nesse ritmo, não vão sobrar\Nmuitos lugares pra morar na cidade.{Gal}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.99,0:15:53.81,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{I see... Even this pretty floating city\Nhas hardships too, huh? - OG}Hm... Então mesmo essa linda cidade\Nflutuante tem suas dificuldades.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.48,0:16:00.27,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{But, well, if push comes to shove, you can take the sea train and go live somewhere. - OG}Mas se der ruim, dá pra pegar o sea\Ntrain e ir morar em outro lugar.{Z/Gal}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.27,0:16:04.42,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{You can say that... now. - OG}Isso é uma opção...\NBom, agora é, pelo menos.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.42,0:16:08.93,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{But it was only a bit over a decade ago\Nthat the sea train was created.}Mas o sea train só existe\Nhá pouco mais de uma década.{Gal}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.93,0:16:13.96,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Before that time, it wasn't quite that easy to get across the sea. - OG}Antes disso, não era tão simples\Nassim cruzar o mar.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.96,0:16:14.70,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Hã?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.62,0:16:18.82,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Naturally, people were rarely able to go back\Nand forth between the islands. - OG}Naturalmente, era raro alguém\Nviajar entre as ilhas.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.82,0:16:22.16,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{On this isolated island, - OG}A ilha vivia isolada,{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.16,0:16:28.18,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{the residents vaguely imagined\Ntheir land being submerged someday and grew completely hopeless. - OG}{\q2}e os moradores perdiam a esperança imaginando\Nsua terra ser engolida pelo mar algum dia.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.69,0:16:42.52,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{What relieved people's\Nworries even about the future - OG}O que aliviou os medos das pessoas sobre o futuro{Gal}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.52,0:16:45.57,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,foi o sea train, {\i1}Puffing Tom{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.57,0:16:49.76,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{You can now go across the sea\Nwhenever you want without a log pose. - OG}Agora era possível cruzar o mar quando\Nquisesse, sem precisar de log pose.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.76,0:16:51.99,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{So this was big progress! - OG}Isso foi um grande progresso!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.61,0:16:58.75,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Tudo graças ao criador do sea train,\Num grande carpinteiro naval chamado Tom.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.19,0:17:04.16,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{We were all saved by him. - OG}Ele salvou todos nós.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.22,0:17:14.10,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Bro!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.18,0:17:18.48,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Socorro...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.39,0:17:27.87,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Vou mandar um "oi" pro "Bro" por vocês.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.96,0:17:40.46,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{We now know the location. - OG}Temos a localização.{JT}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.46,0:17:46.21,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Vamos.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.17,0:18:06.23,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Ai!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.57,0:18:09.13,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Ai, ai, ai...!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.20,0:18:13.24,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{So, brother... - OG}Então, irmãozinho...{JT}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.24,0:18:13.86,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Hm? - OG}Hã?{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.54,0:18:16.07,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{I'm gonna get to the main issue. - OG}Vou direto ao ponto.{Gal}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.69,0:18:19.59,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,O que você vai fazer depois de consertar esse navio?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.23,0:18:21.55,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,O que eu vou fazer?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.55,0:18:23.80,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Of course, I'll go on an adventure with her again, - OG}Vou sair em aventura com ela de novo,{Gal}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.80,0:18:26.84,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,e um dia voltaremos pro nosso lar,\No East Blue!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.81,0:18:30.30,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{It's not like we went around the world, - OG}Não é como se tivéssemos dado a volta ao mundo,{Gal}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.30,0:18:32.84,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,mas é um navio que viajou pela Grand Line.{OG}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.84,0:18:35.98,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{It'll be good enough\Nto call it a triumphant return. - OG}Já dá pra chamar de\Nretorno triunfante.{Gal}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.98,0:18:37.48,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Vou erguer a cabeça e–
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.48,0:18:40.06,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{No, you won't be able to go back... - OG}Não! Não tem como voltar...{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.60,0:18:42.73,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,pro East Blue.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.75,0:18:45.81,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{To begin with, it's too far. - OG}É longe demais.{Gal}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.15,0:18:51.07,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Bro?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.99,0:18:56.57,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Quando puxamos o navio pra cá antes,{OG}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.57,0:18:58.95,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{I was observing her very carefully. - OG}eu dei uma boa olhada nela.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.95,0:19:01.20,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Esse navio está no fim da vida.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.20,0:19:03.90,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{The assessment by Galley-La is correct. - OG}A avaliação da Galley-La está certíssima.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.90,0:19:06.30,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{As someone who's in the dismantling business, - OG}Ouça quem é do ramo de desmonte...{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.30,0:19:08.00,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{I suggest you demolish her. - OG}Eu sugiro desmontá-la.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.71,0:19:10.92,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,O quê...? Isso é ridículo!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.30,0:19:15.33,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Eu te ajudo a desmontar seu navio!{OG}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.33,0:19:18.26,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,O quê?! O que está dizendo, seu idiota?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.99,0:19:22.05,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Espera! O que está fazendo?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.05,0:19:23.56,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Para aí!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.56,0:19:24.43,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,– Bro!\N– Bro!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.43,0:19:28.66,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{I'm just saying I'll help you demolish that ship. - OG}É só uma oferta amigável\Npra ajudar a desmontar seu navio.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.66,0:19:32.32,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Don't be ridiculous! I won't allow that! - OG}Não seja ridículo! Eu não vou permitir!{Gal}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.95,0:19:35.32,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,A {\i1}Merry{\i0} é meu navio!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.61,0:19:38.57,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{No...! She's... - OG}Ela não é! Na verdade...{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.57,0:19:41.03,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{no longer a ship. - OG}ela não é mais um navio.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.36,0:19:42.22,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{What? - OG}O quê...?{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.87,0:19:44.37,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,O que disse?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.37,0:19:50.47,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Eu te perguntei o que ia fazer depois de\Nconsertar esse navio, lembra?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.47,0:19:55.89,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{If you were going to offer your life\Nto the sea with this ship, -OG}Se fosse sair pro mar\Npra morrer com esse navio,{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.89,0:19:59.09,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,eu não teria dito nada.{OG}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.51,0:20:05.64,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Mas... você disse que queria\Nvoltar pro East Blue nesse navio.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.64,0:20:09.69,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{So I'm trying to stop you... brother. - OG}Então estou te impedindo agora... irmãozinho.{JT}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.71,0:20:16.78,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{This ship... can no longer\Neven reach the next shore. - OG}Esse navio... nem vai chegar\Nà próxima ilha.{Gal}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.35,0:20:24.38,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Listen. Ships are born with a promise\Nto carry you across the sea - OG}Escute. Navios nascem com a promessa\Nde te levar pelo mar{Gal}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.38,0:20:27.67,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,de uma costa à outra.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.67,0:20:32.13,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{In other words, once a ship can\Nno longer carry you to shore... - OG}Ou seja, quando um navio não\Nconsegue mais te levar à costa...{JT}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.63,0:20:37.13,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Ei!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.13,0:20:38.80,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Para com isso!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.80,0:20:42.05,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Quando ela não pode mais te levar à costa...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.05,0:20:43.93,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,ela não é mais um navio!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.43,0:20:46.77,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,– Bro!\N– Bro!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.65,0:20:57.78,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Para com isso!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.54,0:21:12.54,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{You bastard! Move away from Merry! - OG}Seu maldito! Saia de perto da {\i1}Merry{\i0}!{JT}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.59,0:21:26.38,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{You son of a bitch! - OG}Seu idiota cabeça-dura!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.76,0:21:30.19,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{If you don't get it... - OG}Se não quer ouvir...{Gal}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.07,0:21:37.65,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{take a good look at her... - OG}então olhe bem pra ela...{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.65,0:21:40.36,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,com seus próprios olhos!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.59,0:24:26.67,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Desculpa, {\i1}Merry{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.93,0:24:32.32,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Vou te consertar agora.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.93,0:24:35.91,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Vou te consertar agora...\NEu vou...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.32,0:24:38.58,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,quantas vezes precisar...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.40,0:24:43.04,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Vou te consertar quantas vezes precisar!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.06,0:24:46.01,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Quantas vezes precisar!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.68,0:24:52.92,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Ei! Já chega, narigudo!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.92,0:24:54.80,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Você viu o fundo do navio, não viu?!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.80,0:24:59.73,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{With the broken keel at the root of her, the outer panels\Nare breaking free, and the frames are falling apart! - OG}Com a quilha quebrada, os painéis externos estão\Nse soltando e as cavernas estão desmoronando!{Z/JT}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:59.73,0:25:03.31,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{When a ship is like that, she'll just fall apart\Nfrom the outside with each wave! - OG}Um navio assim se despedaça\Npor fora a cada onda.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:03.87,0:25:07.07,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{And yet, you think\Na total amateur like you can... - OG}E mesmo assim, um amador completo\Ncomo você acha que pode–{JT}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.59,0:25:18.05,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Shut up! - OG}Cala a boca!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.05,0:25:20.75,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Não quero ouvir mais nada!{OG}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:20.75,0:25:24.84,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Keep your mouth shut,\Nor I'll beat you up, you hooligan! - OG}Fecha essa boca ou eu fecho\Npor você, seu bandido!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:34.19,0:25:35.01,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{At... - OG}Lá no...{Gal}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:38.19,0:25:39.84,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{At heart... - OG}Lá no fundo...{Gal}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.55,0:25:43.86,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{I know it. - OG}Eu já sabia...{Gal}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:43.86,0:25:46.57,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Hã?! O que disse?!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:47.46,0:25:48.65,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{At heart... - OG}Lá no fundo...{Gal}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:51.23,0:25:54.89,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{At heart... I know it all. - OG}Lá no fundo... eu já sabia.{Gal}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:56.58,0:26:01.41,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{I know that Merry is at the end of her life! - OG}Eu sei que a {\i1}Merry{\i0} está no fim da vida!{Gal}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:06.19,0:26:07.58,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{At heart... - OG}Lá no fundo...{Gal}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:09.21,0:26:12.55,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Eu... sabia...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:13.72,0:26:16.39,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Quando ouvi a avaliação...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:16.91,0:26:22.00,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{I was convinced that what I saw\Non that day really happened. - OG}Finalmente me convenci de que\No que vi naquele dia realmente aconteceu.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:23.12,0:26:26.84,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{First, I thought I was dreaming. - OG}No início, achei que era um sonho.{JT}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:26.84,0:26:30.05,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{I thought there was no way\Nsomething like that could happen. - OG}Pensei: "O que estou vendo não pode ser real."{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:31.73,0:26:36.84,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{On one foggy night...\Nin a forest under the moonlight. - OG}Numa noite de neblina...\Nnuma floresta sob o luar,{Gal}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:36.84,0:26:39.83,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Ouvi as batidas de um martelo de madeira.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:40.47,0:26:45.38,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{It came from the ship, although no one was supposed to \Nbe on her at the time. - OG}Vinham do navio, mesmo que ninguém\Ndeveria estar a bordo.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:46.04,0:26:52.76,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Esse som vinha do nosso\Nnavio avariado e encalhado.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.37,0:26:57.60,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{It was very foggy,\Nbut I definitely saw someone there... - OG}Apesar da neblina densa,\Neu definitivamente vi alguém lá,{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.60,0:27:00.10,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{striking a wooden hammer. - OG}usando um martelo de madeira.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:00.10,0:27:04.02,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{I couldn't figure out who it was. - OG}Eu simplesmente... não consegui identificar quem era.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:06.29,0:27:09.27,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{But then, when\Nthe morning came the next day, -OG}Mas então, quando amanheceu,{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:09.27,0:27:13.25,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{the ship was lousily fixed. - OG}apesar do trabalho malfeito, o navio estava consertado.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:13.25,0:27:16.07,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{The completely broken mast\Nwas also fixed as it used to be. - OG}O mastro quebrado também foi\Nrestaurado à forma original.{Gal}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:16.07,0:27:19.58,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{But the really mysterious thing was that... - OG}Mas o verdadeiro mistério foi que...{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:20.74,0:27:26.71,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{whoever fixed the Merry knew how she originally looked. - OG}quem consertou a {\i1}Merry{\i0}\Nconhecia seu design original.{Gal}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:26.71,0:27:29.73,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Apesar de todas as modificações que fizemos,{Gal}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:29.73,0:27:33.57,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{this person put the Merry back\Nto how she used to look!}alguém restaurou a {\i1}Merry{\i0}\Nà aparência original!{Gal}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:36.41,0:27:38.51,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Everything was a mystery to us, but... - OG}Foi tudo um grande mistério pra nós, mas...{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:38.51,0:27:42.06,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{for some reason,\Nthese words remained in my heart. - OG}por algum motivo, aquelas palavras\Nficaram no meu coração.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:42.90,0:27:47.52,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{I don't even know if this person actually said it\Nor I was imagining things... - OG}Nem sei se a pessoa que vi realmente\Ndisse aquilo, ou se eu estava imaginando...{Z/Gal}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:49.42,0:27:50.48,Flashbacks-207+,,0,0,0,,Não se preocupe.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:53.51,0:27:56.82,Flashbacks-207+,,0,0,0,,{\t(1500,3290,1,\3c&HF9F7F6&\4c&HF9F7F6&)}Eu carrego vocês por mais um tempinho.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:58.85,0:28:01.15,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Pode parecer bobagem, mas...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.22,0:28:08.88,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{I feel that it might've been\Nan incarnation of the Merry. - OG}Eu... sinto que pode ter sido\Numa encarnação da {\i1}Merry{\i0}.{Z/Gal}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:13.33,0:28:17.80,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{I bet the ship was already at her limits then. - OG}Aposto que ela já estava no limite naquela época.{Gal}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:17.80,0:28:23.37,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{So she might've turned into\Nthat form to let us know it. - OG}Então talvez tenha assumido\Nessa forma pra nos avisar.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:25.57,0:28:29.60,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Quando ouvi a avaliação,\Nsó pensei nisso.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:33.57,0:28:37.61,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Você acha que sou maluco, né?\NNão precisa acreditar.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:40.45,0:28:41.70,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Bro?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:42.51,0:28:44.62,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Acreditar...?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:45.07,0:28:49.67,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Essa pessoa parecia um marinheiro\Nsegurando um martelo de madeira, certo?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.13,0:28:52.22,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,O quê...? Como...?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:52.22,0:28:53.25,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Você sabe?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:54.91,0:28:56.63,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Brother... - OG}Irmãozinho...{JT}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:56.63,0:28:59.43,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,você viu um {\i1}klabautermann{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:00.11,0:29:02.12,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,K-Klabau...?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:03.18,0:29:05.52,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Klabautermann. - OG}O {\i1}klabautermann{\i0}.{Gal}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:05.52,0:29:08.56,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{It's one of the legends known among sailors. - OG}É uma lenda conhecida entre marinheiros.{Gal}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.23,0:29:14.22,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{It's a sprite that dwells only lives\Nin ships treated with great care. - OG}É um espírito que só habita navios\Ntratados com muito carinho.{Gal}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:14.22,0:29:16.62,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{I suppose you could say\Nit's a ship's incarnation. - OG}Então sim, é como uma encarnação do navio.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:18.47,0:29:22.79,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{They carry wooden hammers in their hands and are dressed in sailor's raincoats. - OG}Carregam um martelo de madeira\Ne vestem capa de marinheiro.{Z/JT}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:22.79,0:29:24.47,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{When danger approaches the ship, - OG}Quando o perigo se aproxima,{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:24.47,0:29:28.04,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{\t(2504,3570,\c&H000000&)}{they run around inside the ship\Nand let people know about it. - OG}eles correm pelo navio\Npra avisar a tripulação.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:28.04,0:29:32.42,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{It is said that they sometimes help sailors quite a bit. - OG}Dizem que às vezes ajudam\Nmuito os marinheiros.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:32.42,0:29:36.84,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{But to be honest, this is the first time I've heard someone say they saw one. - OG}Mas sinceramente, essa é a primeira vez que ouço\Nalguém dizer que viu um.{Gal}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:38.82,0:29:43.30,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{The more care the ship receives,\Nthe more it appreciates the sailors. - OG}Quanto mais carinho o navio recebe,\Nmais ele aprecia sua tripulação.{Gal}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:44.00,0:29:49.27,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Esse navio deve ter querido garantir\Nque vocês chegassem à próxima ilha.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:49.27,0:29:54.74,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{She was able to encounter a crew she wanted to carry so badly - OG}Ela encontrou uma tripulação que queria\Nlevar com tanto afinco{Gal}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:54.74,0:29:58.41,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{that she'd borrow a human form to appear... - OG}que assumiu forma humana.{Gal}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:58.41,0:30:01.74,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Aposto que ela tem sido muito feliz.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:06.96,0:30:08.45,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Merry{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:14.08,0:30:15.46,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Entendo...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:16.21,0:30:17.67,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Então, aquele...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:18.41,0:30:21.17,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,que falou comigo naquele dia...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:21.99,0:30:24.01,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{was really you, huh? - OG}realmente {\i1}era{\i0} você, né?{JT}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:24.59,0:30:25.86,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Merry{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:35.44,0:30:38.65,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{At any rate, for Heaven's sake... - OG}Mas você só pode estar brincando...{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:39.13,0:30:45.60,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{You had a big fight with your friends\Nknowing your ship is at her limits, then? - OG}{\q2}Você brigou feio com seus amigos\Nmesmo sabendo que o navio estava no limite?{JT}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:47.85,0:30:50.50,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Não é tão simples assim.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:50.87,0:30:54.28,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{How inept men are! - OG}Homens são tão ineptos!{Gal}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:54.28,0:30:55.92,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,São uns idiotas!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:04.73,0:31:06.82,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Parece que tem alguém aí.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:08.00,0:31:12.14,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Someone's here"? Who else could it be\Nbut Zambai and the others! - OG}"Alguém"?\NDevem ser o Zambai e os outros!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:12.71,0:31:16.28,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Why did they take the trouble\Nof coming from the sea side? - OG}Por que estão vindo pelo lado do mar?{Gal}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:16.28,0:31:21.00,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Yeah... when they usually use\Nthe upper entrance... - OG}É... normalmente eles vêm\Npela entrada de cima...{JT}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:21.00,0:31:23.86,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{They might've brought Straw Hat. - OG}Talvez trouxeram o Chapéu de Palha.{JT}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:23.86,0:31:25.36,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Ah, é verdade!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:25.36,0:31:29.16,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{I forgot that I sent for Straw Hat\Nand the others with you as bait! - OG}Esqueci que usei você como isca\Npra atrair os Chapéus de Palha!{Gal}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:29.64,0:31:33.34,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Eles não vão vir. Não somos mais amigos.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:33.34,0:31:34.87,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{I told you so, didn't I? - OG}Eu já disse isso, lembra?{Gal}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:41.07,0:31:43.80,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Por que não estão entrando?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:44.76,0:31:47.84,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Okay, okay. I'll open the door now! - OG}Tá bom, tá bom. Já vou abrir!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:49.27,0:31:52.56,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Okay, okay. Geez, stop ringing the bell! - OG}Tá bom, tá bom... Ei, para com isso!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:57.28,0:32:01.02,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Brother... Go back to your friends. - OG}Escuta, irmãozinho... Volta pros seus amigos.{JT}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:03.65,0:32:08.00,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{I can't do that now.\NI fought a duel with my captain. - OG}Não posso fazer isso agora. Duelei com meu capitão.{Gal}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:08.00,0:32:10.66,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Além disso, a questão do navio ainda não foi resolvida, então...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:12.61,0:32:15.00,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,O que quer dizer com não foi resolvida?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:15.00,0:32:20.08,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{If you know that your ship can't\Nsail anymore, it's simple, isn't it? - OG}Se sabe que seu navio não pode\Nmais navegar, é simples, não é?{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:24.23,0:32:26.30,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Deixe ela comigo.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:26.30,0:32:29.18,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{I'll take care of her in a way\Nthat you'd appreciate. - OG}Vou cuidar dela de um jeito\Nque você vai apreciar.{Gal}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:29.74,0:32:31.54,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{What I did earlier, too, you know... - OG}E o que fiz mais cedo...{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:31.54,0:32:36.55,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{I tried to destroy the ship thinking\Nthat it would be best for you. - OG}Achei que desmontar o navio\Npor você seria o melhor.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:36.55,0:32:39.31,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Não se meta!\NÉ problema meu!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:39.31,0:32:43.42,Secondary-207+,,0,0,0,,{\an8}Ei, estou tentando resolver seu problema!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:40.37,0:32:42.42,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Zambai?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:43.42,0:32:44.65,Secondary-207+,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{You should appreciate it! - OG}Seja mais grato!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:44.65,0:32:47.84,Secondary-207+,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{I should appreciate it? Give me a break!}Grato? Me poupe!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.78,0:32:53.52,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Você não entende?!\NÉ um incômodo pro navio também!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:53.52,0:32:58.02,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Ela ama tanto vocês que\Napareceu em forma humana.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:58.02,0:33:01.96,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Se ela afundar no meio do mar\Ncom vocês a bordo...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:01.96,0:33:07.42,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Ei! Se isso acontecer, mesmo depois de morrer,\Nela não vai descansar em paz!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:07.85,0:33:11.44,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Então, quando {\i1}seus{\i0} amigos estiverem morrendo,\Nvocê consegue simplesmente ir embora dizendo:
Dialogue: 0,0:33:11.44,0:33:15.16,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,"Bom, espero que pelo menos\Nmorra sem sofrer"?!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:15.16,0:33:18.81,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{If you put it that way,\Nthat's a whole different discussion! - OG}O que você está sugerindo\Né algo completamente diferente!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:18.81,0:33:21.89,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{No, it's not! It's that kind of matter!}Nada disso! É exatamente a mesma coisa!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:21.89,0:33:23.86,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{You just don't get it, do you?! - OG}O que preciso fazer pra você entender, seu...?!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:28.15,0:33:29.45,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,– Hã?!\N– Hã?!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:29.45,0:33:30.91,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Mozu!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:36.39,0:33:37.20,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Kiwi!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:37.20,0:33:40.12,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Pardon me... for interrupting. - OG}Desculpem a interrupção.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:44.61,0:33:48.12,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,É que essas duas moças não nos deixaram entrar, então...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:48.12,0:33:52.09,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{What the hell are you bastards doing here?! - OG}Que droga vocês estão fazendo aqui?!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:55.63,0:33:56.31,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{\fad(150,150)}Iron Body!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:56.31,0:33:58.43,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Hm? You son of a bitch! - OG}Hã? Que diabos?!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:02.27,0:34:06.02,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Blueno! Qual o sentido de–
Dialogue: 0,0:34:06.62,0:34:10.23,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Hã? O que é isso? Que atrevimento!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:10.23,0:34:13.17,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Quem você pensa que eu sou?!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:14.12,0:34:17.58,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Who are you trying to pick a fight with?! - OG}Sabe com quem está\Narrumando briga?!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:20.41,0:34:23.55,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{You're only a dull bar owner! - OG}Você é só o dono de um bar qualquer!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:23.55,0:34:25.88,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{What's up with those clothes? - OG}Que roupa é essa?!{Gal}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:25.88,0:34:30.09,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{You seem different from your usual self! - OG}Está agindo estranho! O que houve?!{Gal}
Comment: 0,0:34:30.09,0:34:30.92,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Tch.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:33.10,0:34:34.97,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Chega, Blueno.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:42.39,0:34:44.68,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,E-Ei! V-Você tá bem?!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:44.68,0:34:48.39,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Não podemos matá-lo ainda.\NNão esqueça da missão.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:44.68,0:34:46.12,Secondary-207+,,0,0,0,,{\an8}Aguenta firme!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:48.39,0:34:49.11,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Desculpe.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:49.11,0:34:51.44,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Q-Q-Que está acontecendo?! Ei!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:51.85,0:34:54.91,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{I thought I saw them working at the shipyard! - OG}Eu juro que vi eles trabalhando no estaleiro!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:54.91,0:34:57.53,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{What the hell? Why was he able to... - OG}Que droga? Como ele conseguiu...?{Gal}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:57.53,0:35:02.50,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{You bastards! What are you people?! You sure are acting pretty super, aren't you?! - OG}O que vocês {\i1}são{\i0}?! Estão se achando\Nbem super, não estão?!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:02.50,0:35:08.96,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{How dare you hurt innocent girls?!\NThey're like my little sisters, you jerks! - OG}Como ousam machucar garotas inocentes?!\NElas são como minhas irmãs, seus idiotas!{JT}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:08.96,0:35:13.42,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{To start with, how the hell\Ndo you know about this place? This is my secret base! - OG}E como diabos sabem desse lugar?\NEssa é minha base secreta!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:13.91,0:35:18.33,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{We don't care about that.\NI'll keep this simple. Listen carefully. - OG}Nada disso importa.\NVou ser direto, então escute bem.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:18.33,0:35:21.06,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Nossas vidas nesta cidade eram uma fachada.{OG}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:21.06,0:35:24.69,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{In reality, we are World Government\Nintelligence agents. - OG}Na verdade, somos agentes de\Ninteligência do Governo Mundial.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:25.48,0:35:28.45,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Você deve saber o que isso significa...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:28.45,0:35:30.90,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,assim como o motivo de estarmos aqui.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:31.28,0:35:34.07,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Franky, já sabemos de tudo.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:34.81,0:35:36.91,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Cutty Flam...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:36.91,0:35:41.29,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Tom's other disciple, who was said to have died eight years ago... - OG}O outro aprendiz de Tom, que supostamente\Nmorreu oito anos atrás...{Gal}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:41.96,0:35:43.61,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,É você.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:45.16,0:35:49.31,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{I don't know how you found\Nthat out... but that's splendid. - OG}Não sei como descobriram,\Nmas é impressionante.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:49.31,0:35:52.27,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{At the same time, I'm starting to feel uneasy. - OG}Ao mesmo tempo, é bem preocupante.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:53.21,0:35:56.59,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Aquele idiota do Iceburg está bem?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:56.59,0:35:57.55,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Nós o matamos.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:00.14,0:36:02.52,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Don't try to play innocent now... - OG}Não tente se fazer de bobo agora...{Gal}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:03.25,0:36:05.39,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{as we already know everything. - OG}Nós já sabemos de tudo.{JT}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:07.08,0:36:09.83,Flashbacks-207+,,0,0,0,,É questão de tempo até\Nvirem atrás de mim.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:10.70,0:36:13.82,Flashbacks-207+,,0,0,0,,Leve-as e saia da ilha, Franky.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:13.82,0:36:19.53,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Tom as passou pro Iceburg...\Ne o Iceburg pra você.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:20.70,0:36:22.74,Flashbacks-207+,,0,0,0,,Vocês dois, venham aqui.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:22.74,0:36:25.25,Flashbacks-207+,,0,0,0,,Quero confiar algo\Nimportante a vocês dois.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:25.67,0:36:29.37,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Nossa missão demorou bastante,\Nmas finalmente é xeque-mate.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:29.37,0:36:35.57,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Agora, entregue as plantas da\Narma ancestral Pluton, Cutty Flam.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:37.06,0:36:39.72,Flashbacks-207+,,0,0,0,,Flam...? Que nome estranho.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:40.08,0:36:42.05,Flashbacks-207+,,0,0,0,,{"Franky" would do, right? "Franky" would. - OG}"Franky" serve, né? "Franky", então.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:42.63,0:36:44.17,Flashbacks-207+,,0,0,0,,Qualquer coisa serve.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:44.17,0:36:46.27,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Está me ouvindo?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:46.27,0:36:49.45,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{I'm saying hand them over to us, Cutty Flam. - OG}Estou mandando você entregá-las, Cutty Flam.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:50.44,0:36:53.32,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Não tenho nada pra dar a vocês, idiotas!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:56.19,0:36:57.15,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,O quê...?!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:05.41,0:37:09.67,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Wh-What just happened?!\NIt was so fast that I couldn't see anything. - OG}Q-Que aconteceu?!\NFoi tão rápido que não vi nada.{Gal}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:10.56,0:37:12.88,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Ei! V-Você tá bem?!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:18.03,0:37:19.86,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Isso é...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:19.86,0:37:21.34,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,O que foi, Lucci?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:21.84,0:37:24.56,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,O que é esse cômodo imundo?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:24.95,0:37:26.52,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Uma sala de projetos?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:26.52,0:37:28.23,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Oh?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:28.23,0:37:31.81,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Bom lugar pra esconder plantas. Encontrem!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:42.11,0:37:44.58,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Esses são... crachás?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:45.37,0:37:47.04,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Cutty Flam.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:47.04,0:37:48.66,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Iceburg.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:48.66,0:37:49.91,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Tom.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:49.91,0:37:51.42,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Esse nome é...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:54.37,0:37:55.59,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Isso é...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:56.84,0:37:59.47,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Don't you dare touch it! - OG}Não ouse tocar nisso!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:01.01,0:38:05.72,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Don't intrude upon someone's memories! - OG}Não se meta nas memórias dos outros!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:05.72,0:38:09.43,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{This is where we grew up. - OG}Fomos criados aqui.{Gal}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:09.43,0:38:16.02,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{It was the shipbuilding company, Tom's Workers! It's the home of the world's best shipwright! - OG}{\q2}Essa era a empresa de construção naval Tom's Workers,\No lar do melhor carpinteiro do mundo!{Z}
